726383f-a.text:
Cooper Ave., at the N.W. corner of 72nd Place, showing the Tilly house. Eugene L. Armbruster states its old number was 7 Copeland Ave., its new number is 2941. However, if this house still stands in 1929 it
is no longer at the corner, but at 7211 Cooper Ave.
March 31, 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726382f-a.text:
Cooper Ave., at the N.W. corner of 72nd Place (white house thereon), showing the former J. S. Siney house of 1860. Edward Brochere was a later occupant. In 1927 the Glendale Square Club was housed here.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
